        <glossentry
            id="glos-webdav">
            <glossterm>WebDAV</glossterm>
            <glossdef>
                <para>Web-based Distributed Authoring and Versioning. WebDAV is a set of extensions to the 
                    Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP) that allows users to edit and manage files 
                    collaboratively on remote World Wide Web servers.</para>
            </glossdef>
        </glossentry>
        <glossentry
            id="glos-oaipmh">
            <glossterm>OAI-PMH</glossterm>
            <glossdef>
                <para>Open Archive Initiative Protocol for Metadata Harvesting. 
                    It is a protocol developed by the Open Archives Initiative. 
                    It is used to harvest (or collect) the metadata descriptions 
                    of the records in an archive so that services can be built using 
                    metadata from many archives.</para>
            </glossdef>
        </glossentry>
